</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>Then answered     
Bildad the Shuhite, and said,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>   
2</H4></TD><TD><P>How long wilt thou speak these things? and how long shall the 
words of thy mouth be like a strong wind?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>Doth EL pervert judgment? or doth the SHADDAY     
pervert justice?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD> 
<P>If thy children have sinned against him, and he have cast them away for      
their transgression;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD> 
<TD><P>If thou wouldest seek unto EL betimes, and make thy supplication to the  
SHADDAY;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>If    
thou wert pure and upright; surely now he would awake for thee, and make the    
habitation of thy righteousness prosperous.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>Though thy beginning was small, yet thy latter    
end should greatly increase.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>    
8</H4></TD><TD><P>For enquire, I pray thee, of the former age, and prepare      
thyself to the search of their fathers:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A      
NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>(For we are but of yesterday, and know nothing,   
because our days upon earth are a shadow:)</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A   
NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>Shall not they teach thee, and tell thee, and   
utter words out of their heart?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>
11</H4></TD><TD><P>Can the rush grow up without mire? can the flag grow without 
water?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>      
Whilst it is yet in his greenness, and not cut down, it withereth before any    
other herb.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P> 
So are the paths of all that forget EL; and the hypocrite's hope shall          
perish:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>     
Whose hope shall be cut off, and whose trust shall be a spider's web.</P></TD>  
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>He shall lean upon   
his house, but it shall not stand: he shall hold it fast, but it shall not      
endure.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>He   
is green before the sun, and his branch shooteth forth in his garden.</P></TD>  
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>His roots are        
wrapped about the heap, and seeth the place of stones.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>If he destroy him from his place, 
then it shall deny him, saying, I have not seen thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD      
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>Behold, this is the joy of his    
way, and out of the earth shall others grow.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>Behold, EL will not cast away a perfect man,    
neither will he help the evil doers:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A         
NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>Till he fill thy mouth with laughing, and thy   
lips with rejoicing.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4>    
</TD><TD><P>They that hate thee shall be clothed with shame; and the dwelling   
place of the wicked shall come to nought.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This         
